  "prompt": "Where can I get best quality Build In Wardrobes in Guildford?",
  "response": "If you're looking for high-quality built-in wardrobes in Guildford, you have several great options. Here are some recommendations:\n\n### 1. **Sharps (Guildford)**  \n   - **Why?** Sharps is a well-known brand specializing in bespoke fitted furniture, including wardrobes. They offer excellent quality, tailored designs, and a wide range of finishes.  \n   - **Location:** You can visit their showroom in Guildford or arrange a home consultation.  \n   - **Website:** [www.sharps.co.uk](https://www.sharps.co.uk)\n\n### 2. **Aston Matthews**  \n   - **Why?** They provide luxurious, high-end fitted wardrobes with a focus on craftsmanship and bespoke designs. Ideal if you\u2019re looking for something premium.  \n   - **Location:** Based in Farnham, close to Guildford, with a showroom you can visit.  \n   - **Website:** [www.astonmatthews.com](https://www.astonmatthews.com)\n\n### 3. **The Surrey Handyman Company**  \n   - **Why?** A local company that offers custom-built wardrobes tailored to your space and style. They focus on quality craftsmanship and personal service.  \n   - **Location:** Serving Guildford and surrounding areas.  \n   - **Website:** [www.surreyhandyman.co.uk](https://www.surreyhandyman.co.uk)\n\n### 4. **Impey Interiors**  \n   - **Why?** A family-run business offering bespoke wardrobes and fitted furniture with attention to detail and high-quality materials.  \n   - **Location:** Based in Woking, close to Guildford.  \n   - **Website:** [www.impeyinteriors.co.uk](https://www.impeyinteriors.co.uk)\n\n### 5. **Homebase (Guildford)**  \n   - **Why?** While not bespoke, Homebase offers a range of wardrobe solutions that can be customized to fit your space. It\u2019s a more budget-friendly option.  \n   - **Location:** Guildford store or online.  \n   - **Website:** [www.homebase.co.uk](https://www.homebase.co.uk)\n\n### 6. **Local Carpenters and Joiners**  \n   - **Why?** For a truly bespoke solution, hiring a skilled local carpenter or joiner can give you exactly what you want. Look for recommendations on platforms like Checkatrade or local Facebook groups.\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Supplier:  \n- **Visit Showrooms:** See the quality of materials and finishes in person.  \n- **Check Reviews:** Look for customer feedback online.  \n- **Get Multiple Quotes:** Compare prices and designs before making a decision.  \n- **Consider Longevity:** Invest in durable materials and construction for a wardrobe that lasts.\n\nLet me know if you'd like more details about any of these options!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
